qcNotes:
Complex, but reproducible mixture of at least 175 distinct  C10-chloro compounds, having an approximate overall empirical formula of C10 H10 Cl8.; the 2 most active components are a C10H10Cl8 compound and a C10H11Cl7 compound which had been elucidated as 2,2,5-endo,6-exo,8,9,10-heptachlorobornane. Produced by the chlorination of camphene to 67-69% chlorine by weight and made up of compds. of C10 H8 Cl10, C10 H18-n Cl n (mostly poychloroboranes) and C10  H16-n  Cl n (oychloroboranes and/or polychlorotricyclenes) with n = 6 to 9
